!/tests/test_training_data_quality.py


# =============================================================================
# H. Intentionally private by default
# =============================================================================
#
# The root deny rule already covers these categories. They are listed here as
# policy documentation, not as additional matching rules:
#
# - data/, experiments/, runtime/, tmp/, outputs/, artifacts/ and real media;
# - cookie/, cookie-catch/, secrets, browser profiles and all credentials;
# - report/V01/, report/V02/, runs/V01/ and runs/V02/ contents;
# - project-specific seed builders and private source adapters;
# - Optmize/workflows/, Optmize/old-plan/ and unreviewed optimization drafts;
# - local manifests/path maps, IDE state, agent state, caches and virtualenvs;
# - future files under otherwise public directories until explicitly reviewed.
